⦿ .spun — the five-fold spin of Samus Aran
node MET · MET · ⟦Samus Aran:MET:2d808b⟧

WHO   — Samus Aran — the bounty hunter
WHAT  — The lone hunter of the Metroid universe — who descends into planet Zebes to end Mother Brain and the Metroid menace, in the 8-bit original and again in Super Metroid.
WHERE — MET · Metroid  Framework inputs: Metroid (1986) & Super Metroid (1994)  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — Because the Metroids in the wrong hands would end all life; because the Pirates took her family and her world; and because the last baby Metroid thinks her its mother, and she will go back into hell to bring it home.
HOW   — By the Chozo Power Suit and its arm cannon, the Morph Ball, the beams and missiles she gathers in the dark — and by the patience and solitude of a hunter who maps a hostile world alone.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  I hunt alone, in armor the Chozo forged — and beneath the helmet, the hunter is a woman.

